deleverageAccount(address,address,addres.notice: If an account is below the minimum collateral ratio, some amount of vault shares can be redeemed such that they fall back under the minimum collateral ratio. A portion of the redemption will be paid to the receiver (an account specified by the caller).

params.account: the address that will exit the vault
params.liquidator: the address that will receive profits from liquidation
params.redeemData: calldata sent to the vault when redeeming liquidator profits
params.useUnderlying: true if we should use the underlying token

enterVault(address,address,uint256,bool,.notice: Enters the account into the specified vault using the specified fCash amount. Additional data is forwarded to the vault contract.

params.account: the address that will enter the vault
params.fCash: total amount of fCash to borrow to enter the vault
params.maxBorrowRate: maximum interest rate to borrow at
params.vaultData: additional data to pass to the vault contract

exitVault(address,address,uint256,uint25.notice: Exits a vault by redeeming yield tokens, lending to offset fCash debt and then withdrawing any earnings back to the account.

params.account: the address that will exit the vault
params.minLendRate: the minimum rate to lend at
params.useUnderlying: if vault shares should be redeemed to underlying
params.vaultSharesToRedeem: amount of vault tokens to exit

rollVaultPosition(address,address,uint25.notice: Re-enters the vault at a longer dated maturity. There is no way to partially re-enter a vault, the account's entire position will be rolled forward.

params.account: the address that will reenter the vault
params.fCashToBorrow: amount of fCash to borrow in the next maturity
params.opts: struct with slippage limits and data to send to vault
params.vaultSharesToRedeem: the amount of vault shares to redeem for asset tokens
